---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Navbar from "../components/Navbar.astro";
import ProcessCarousel from "../components/ProcessCarousel.astro";
import Button from "../components/Button.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import process6 from "../assets/Process/process6.png";
---

<Layout
  title="Process"
  description="Explore the intricate process behind Mechi Carpets' hand-knotted Tibetan rugs. From selecting the finest materials to the skilled hands of our artisans, discover the artistry woven into every piece."
>
  <Navbar />

  <section>
    <div id="container">
      <article id="article-one">
        <h3>
          THE HERITAGE <span class="mobile-breaks"></span>OF TIBETAN
          CRAFTSMANSHIP: <span class="mobile-breaks"></span>OUR RUGS TELL A
          STORY
        </h3>
        <p id="sub-heading">
          Discover the story woven into every rug, and let one of our
          hand-knotted Tibetan rugs bring timeless elegance to your space.
        </p>

        <div id="mobile-carousel-container">
          <ProcessCarousel />
        </div>

        <div id="paragraph">
          <p>
            At Mechi Surshar Carpet Industries, we take pride in the timeless
            tradition of hand-knotting Tibetan rugs, creating masterpieces that
            blend centuries-old craftsmanship with modern elegance. Our journey
            began with a deep respect for the artistry and skill that has been
            passed down through generations of Tibetan artisans.
            <span class="mobile-breaks"><br /></span>
            Each rug we offer is not just a piece of home décor but a testament to
            the dedication and passion of the artisans who pour their hearts into
            every knot.<br />
            <span class="expandable-content">
              <br />
              The process of creating our hand-knotted Tibetan rugs is meticulous
              and labor-intensive. Using the finest natural materials such as wool
              and silk, each rug is crafted with care and precision.
            </span>
          </p>

          <button class="read-more-btn">Read more</button>
          <p class="expandable-content">
            The intricate knots are tied one by one, ensuring that every pattern
            and design tells a unique story. With colors inspired by the natural
            beauty of the Tibetan landscape and patterns that reflect cultural
            symbolism, our rugs are both a work of art and a functional
            treasure.<br />
            <br />
            We are committed to preserving the authenticity and integrity of the
            Tibetan rug-making tradition, supporting local communities, and providing
            a sustainable and ethical source for these exquisite pieces. From the
            hands of skilled artisans to your home, our rugs bring warmth, beauty,
            and a piece of Tibetan heritage into your life.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <div id="desktop-carousel-container">
        <ProcessCarousel />
      </div>
    </div>
    <Button link="/product" text="See our work" color="#1b1b1c" />
  </section>

  <article id="article-two">
    <p
      style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem; line-height: 120%; letter-spacing: 0.00538rem;"
    >
      The Craftsmanship
    </p>
    <h3 class="article-two-text">
      AT THE HEART OF EVERY RUG ARE THE ARTISANS BEHIND THE CRAFT
    </h3>
    <Image src={process6} alt="Process" height={590} id="article-two-image" />
    <p class="article-two-text">
      We are deeply committed to supporting our artisans and their communities.
      By preserving this age-old craft and providing sustainable livelihoods, we
      honor the rich traditions of weaving while empowering the skilled hands
      that make it all possible.<br />
      <br />
      Our rugs are more than just décor—they carry the stories, dreams, and artistry
      of the individuals who craft them. When you bring one of our creations into
      your home, you celebrate not only the beauty of the rug but also the spirit
      and dedication of the artisans behind it.
    </p>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  section {
    border-top: 1px solid #1b1b1c;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 4.8rem;
    padding: 7rem 5.4rem;
  }

  h3 {
    max-width: 45rem;
  }

  #container {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 3rem;
  }

  #sub-heading {
    color: #1b1b1c;
    font-size: 1.875rem;
    font-style: normal;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 120%;
    letter-spacing: -0.0175rem;
  }

  #article-one {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    max-width: 52rem;
  }

  #paragraph {
    display: flex;
    gap: 2.4rem;
  }

  p {
    flex: 1;
  }

  #article-two {
    background-color: #fffdfd;
    margin: 7.75rem 6.5rem;
    padding-top: 3.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 5rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .article-two-text {
    max-width: 56rem;
  }

  #article-two-image {
    margin-top: 2.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  #mobile-carousel-container {
    display: none;
  }

  .read-more-btn {
    display: none;
  }

  @media screen and (max-width: 480px) {
    section {
      border-top: 0.5px solid #1b1b1c;
      padding: 3rem 2.25rem;
      align-items: center;
      text-align: center;
      gap: 2.25rem;
    }

    #sub-heading {
      color: #656569;
      font-family: "General Sans", sans-serif;
      font-size: 1rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.005rem;
    }

    #container {
      width: 100%;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 2.25rem;
    }

    #article-one {
      gap: 2.25rem;
    }

    #paragraph {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 1.2rem;
    }

    #article-two {
      margin: 0;
      padding: 3rem 2.25rem;
      gap: 2.25rem;
    }

    h3.article-two-text {
      margin-top: -2rem;
    }

    #article-two-image {
      width: 100%;
      height: auto;
      margin: 0;
    }

    #mobile-carousel-container {
      display: block;
    }

    #desktop-carousel-container {
      display: none;
    }

    .read-more-btn {
      display: block;
      cursor: pointer;
      border: none;
      background-color: transparent;
      color: #656569;
      text-align: center;
      font-family: "General Sans";
      font-size: 0.75rem;
      font-style: normal;
      font-weight: 400;
      line-height: 120%;
      letter-spacing: 0.00375rem;
      text-decoration-line: underline;
      text-decoration-style: solid;
      text-decoration-skip-ink: none;
      text-decoration-thickness: auto;
      text-underline-offset: auto;
      text-underline-position: from-font;
    }

    .expandable-content {
      display: none;
    }

    .expandable-content.expanded {
      display: block;
    }
  }
</style>

<script>
  document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", () => {
    const btns = document.querySelectorAll(".read-more-btn");

    btns.forEach((btn) => {
      btn.addEventListener("click", () => {
        const expandableContent = document.querySelectorAll(
          ".expandable-content"
        );
        expandableContent.forEach((a) => a.classList.add("expanded"));
        btn.style.display = "none";
      });
    });
  });
</script>
